    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Before you begin, make the Spicy Pork Ragú batch recipe."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the rice following pack instructions."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Warm the Spicy Pork Ragú in a frying pan over a medium heat until bubbling. Stir through the kidney beans and cook for another 2-3 mins until hot."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a small bowl, mix the mayonnaise with the gochujang and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and black pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Toast the tortillas in a dry frying pan for 30 seconds on each side, until warm and flexible."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To build each burrito, lay a romaine leaf in the centre of each tortilla. Top with the rice, Spicy Pork Ragú, kimchi, and a good drizzle of the Gochujang mayo. Add the second romaine leaf on top.Fold the sides in, then roll up from the bottom. If you like, toast the burrito seam-side down in the hot pan for 1-2 mins to seal and crisp."
